HEADWORD: Peronate
<hw>Per"o*nate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>peronatus</ets> rough-booted, fr. <ets>pero</ets>,
<ets>-onis</ets>, a kind of rough boot.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
term applied to the stipes or stalks of certain fungi which are covered
with a woolly substance which at length becomes powdery.</def>
<rj><au>Henslow.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
